code.kill()
Pause the user code through IPC. This will work only if the user code was executed through Code.run.
   If the user code was executed as a standalone Node process (e.g. node user_code.js),
   it can only be paused through Pubsub.

new CodeEngine(config, [options])
CodeEngine is an abstraction for a "worker" in a ThingsJS network.
A CodeEngine instance connects to the Publish/Subscribe service at the provided URL.
Once connected, CodeEngine listens for incoming commands by subscribing to a unique topic. (e.g. "${engine.id}/cmd")



Param
Type
Description




config
Object
The configuration object used to initialize the CodeEngine instance


config.pubsub_url
string
URL of the Publish/Subscribe service


[options]
Object
Additional options object for customizing the CodeEngine behaviour

[reportResource description]

codeEngine.log()
Augmented console.log function for debugging purposes, the log is published to pubsub
Kind: instance method of CodeEngine
codeEngine.run_code()
"Behaviour" functions
   the reason the following functions are defined in this particular style
   is because we consider these operations to be "behaviour"s in the actor model,
   which can be triggered by external signals. For example in our case the external signal comes from Pubsub.
   Of course, the functions can be called directly as well.
Kind: instance method of CodeEngine

[restore_code description]

[description]
Kind: static property of CodeEngine
CodeEngine.Behaviours
Defines a set of "behaviours" for the CodeEngine. (Actor pattern)
  these behaviours are either triggered via Pubsub or directly called by the instance.
  All of these should return a Promise object that resolves to a JSON-serializable object
  as the result will be transmitted over HTTP/MQTT.
Kind: static property of CodeEngine
